10:15 AM Defendant Davin D Rollins in court, in custody.  Attorney John Paul Marchan in court for Davin D Rollins.  Prosecuting attorney Peter Michael Tempelis in court for the State of Wisconsin. 

The Court conducts a colloquy with the Defense.
The Defendant requests a prelim hearing.

Detective Ryan Roeglin, of the Waukesha County Sheriff's Department, sworn in and testifies on direct by ADA Tempelis.
Cross examination by attorney Marchan.
Redirect by ADA Tempelis.

The Court deems testimony closed.

The Defense and objects to bind over.

records.addlTxt: Preliminary hearing on September 26, 2022 at 10:15 am.

11:47 AM; Case called for Review hearing.  Prosecuting attorney Abbey Nickolie in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Davin D Rollins in court, in custody.  Attorney John Paul Marchan in court for Davin D Rollins. Court notes that this matter as well as 21CF1762 & 22CF1184 are set for review hearing with respect to competency, 22CM1507 is set for adjourned initial appearance and the rest of the cases are just tagging along with for status.  Court will first address the review of competency in this matter, 21CF1762 & 22CF1184.

Court notes it has received and reviewed Atty. Marchan's letter filed on 8/9/22 noting that he has reviewed Dr. Bruett's report from the defendant's other matters and he and his client will accept those findings with respect to this matter as well.  Court conducts a colloquy with the defendant regarding his acceptance of Dr. Bruett's report filed in his other matters.  Atty. Nickolie has no objection to a finding of competency.  Court finds the defendant has knowingly, voluntarily, and intelligently waived his right to contest Dr. Bruett's findings.  Court will find that the defendant is competent to proceed.  Court inquires as to a preliminary hearing.  Atty. Marchan notes based on the competency issue time limits were previously tolled/waived.  Preliminary Hearing requested. PRELIMINARY HEARING REQUESTED WITHIN 10 DAYS. Court will adjourn this matter, 21CF1762 & 22CF1184 for preliminary hearing and all other matters will tag along with for status.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 10:15 am.
Review hearing on September 16, 2022 at 11:00 am.

8:56 AM; Case called for Review hearing.   Prosecuting attorney Andrew Nesheim in court for the State of Wisconsin.   Attorney John Paul Marchan in court for Davin D Rollins.  Atty. Marchan provides an update, he notes the defendant is subject to a Chapter 51 in Milwaukee County and is currently being held in Winnebago while that case is pending.  Atty. Marchan requests the matters be adjourned for about 2 weeks to allow time to see where the Chapter 51 case is going.  State has no objection.  Court will adjourn for status in about 2 weeks.  Atty. Marchan will also advise the court that if the defendant is still at Winnebago, and he wants to appear by video, to have that set up for the next court date.
Review hearing scheduled for September 16, 2022 at 11:00 am.

10:07 AM; Case called for Review hearing. Prosecuting attorney Charles Patrick Hoffmann in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Davin D Rollins not in court.  Attorney John Paul Marchan in court for Davin D Rollins. Atty. Marchan notes he was informed by the bailiff that the defendant is out of the jail, with no explanation.  Atty. Marchan advises the court he and his client's position is that they are in-line with Dr. Bruett's last report with a finding of competent to proceed, and he has filed a letter with advising that as well.  Court notes it has received and reviewed Atty. Marchan's letter filed on 08/09/2022.  Atty. Marchan just asks the matter be set over for 10 days to locate his client and be sure he can be present to address all of this on the record.  State has no objection, also noting their position is also in-line with Dr. Bruett's findings as well.  Atty. Marchan also notes that a new competency evaluation was ordered in this matter, 21CF176 & 22CF1184 and is asking that order be withdrawn given the circumstances.  Court will withdraw the most recent order for competency evaluation and will adjourn for continued review hearing.  Court will maintain the previously scheduled review hearing set for 8/29/2022 at 8:30.
Review hearing on August 15, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Filed by Atty. Marchan advises that he and his client will adopt Dr. Bruett's finding that the defendant is competent to proceed and the Court's ruling from the 7/18/22 review hearing finding the defendant competent.  As a result Atty. Marchan is not asking the court to order another competency evaluation.
AMENDED signed by CC Costello on 08/05/2022.
Effective August 1, 2022, this case is assigned to Branch 7 Judicial Vacancy, pursuant to 22-SO-04(67).
Review hearing on August 29, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Order for Competency Evaluation
Attorney John Marchan

Defendant to have no contact with Judge Melvin (except during court on his criminal cases) listed in the Criminal Complaint.    If DNA sample has not been taken from the defendant, the Court orders sample to be taken;  and it may be expunged under 165.77(4) Wis. Statutes.

08:29 AM Defendant Davin D Rollins in court, in custody.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and Court reads complaint to the defendant.  Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties.  Court advises of right to an attorney.  Court tolled time limits for preliminary hearing.  COURT ORDERS FOR COMPETENCY PURSUANT TO SEC.. 971.14(2).  Court grants request and orders the defendant be examined by the Wisconsin Forensic Unit.  To be done as an inpatient/outpatient basis within 30 days.  Review hearing scheduled for August 29, 2022 at 08:30 am.
